## 2. Extract Term Dates to Events Using AI
[Learn more about the Information Extractor]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Data entry is probably the number one reason as to why we need AI/LLMs. This time-consuming and menial task can be completed in seconds and with a high degree of accuracy. Here, we ask the AI to extract each event with the term dates to a list of events using structured output.

## 3. Use Events to Create ICS Document
[Learn more about the code node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Now we have our events, let's create a calendar to put them in. Using the code now, we can construct a simple ICS document - this is the format which can be imported into iCal, Google Calendar and Outlook. For tasks like these, the Code node is best suited to handle custom transformations.

## 4. Create ICS Binary File for Import
[Learn more about the Convert to File node]({{ $env.WEBHOOK_URL }}

Finally with our ICS document ready, we can use the "Convert to File" node to build an ICS binary file which can be shared with team members, classmates or even instructors.
